  "text": "Investigations at a country scale were carried out by [CITATION_1] , and delimited potential regions and degrees of risk based on the environmental affinities of Diaphorina citri, as well as the range and phenology of host plants. In southeastern Mexico, a region characterized by high temperatures (> 25°C) and precipitation (>1100 mm), the potential existence of up to 27 generations were quantified.",
